x4freetext: SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ERR-ANALYS updated in Subents 002,003.
The detecting system consisted of a
telescope formed by a vertical slip 4 mm wide and a
circular back aperture 4 mm in diameter spaced 150 mm
apart from the slit together with a 5 mm thick CsI(Tl)
scintillation crystal mounted on a 6097B-EMI
photomultiplier tube.
An oxygen gaseous target was used. The gas target
chamber consisted of a thin polyethylene bag filled
up to a pressure of 4 mm of mercury over the
atmospheric pressure with commercially pure oxygen.
Energy resolution was 2.5 to 3%.
